title: PhantomParasol: Parasol-type display for ambient and detailed information
title_en: PhantomParasol: Parasol-type display for ambient and detailed information
abstract: 本論文は傘を媒体としたディスプレイによって周辺情報と詳細情報を統合的に提示する手法を提案する。本論文は傘表面に配置したLEDマトリクスとデバイスの回転による視覚残像効果を用いて情報の粒度を滑らかに制御し、移動中の利用者およびその周囲の人々に対して遠距離のアンビエント表示と近距離の詳細表示の両立を実現することを示す。
abstract_en: This paper proposes a parasol-based display technique that integrates ambient and detailed information presentation. This paper demonstrates that a parasol-mounted LED matrix combined with device rotation and persistence-of-vision effects enables smooth control of information granularity to provide both distant ambient displays and near detailed displays for mobile users and nearby people.
positioning_summary: 本研究はモバイル環境における周辺情報と詳細情報の両立の重要性を扱っている。本研究は単一の携帯可能なデバイスで周辺表示と詳細表示を両立させ、移動中の利用者向けに情報の粒度を滑らかに制御する点を位置づけている。
positioning_summary_en: This research addresses the importance of combining ambient and detailed information in mobile environments. This research positions itself as enabling smooth granularity control on a single handheld device to support mobile users by integrating ambient and detailed displays.
purpose_summary: 本研究の目的は傘型ディスプレイで周辺表示と詳細表示を統合し利用者の表示ニーズのギャップを埋めることである。本研究は移動中の利用者とその周囲の人々を対象に、情報の受信負荷や利用状況に応じて表示する情報の粒度を調整することを目標としている。
purpose_summary_en: The objective of this work is to integrate ambient and detailed displays using a parasol-type display to bridge the gap in user display needs. The objective of this work targets mobile users and nearby people and aims to adjust information granularity according to reception load and usage context.
method_summary: 本システムは傘型デバイスに複数のLEDアレイ、ジャイロセンサ、組込みマイコンを搭載し、手に持って回転させることで視覚の残像を利用して詳細情報を提示する仕組みを採用している。本システムは52×52相当のLEDマトリクスやLEDドライバ相当、方位／傾斜センサ相当、マイコン相当を用いてBMP/JPG/PNGを52×52に変換して表示し、GPSや無線ネットワークとの連携も検討している。
method_summary_en: The system uses a parasol device equipped with multiple LED arrays, gyroscopic sensors, and an embedded microcontroller, and it presents detailed information by rotating the device to exploit persistence of vision. The system employs an LED matrix equivalent to 52×52, LED drivers, orientation/inclination sensors, and a microcontroller to convert BMP/JPG/PNG images into 52×52 displays, and it also considers integration with GPS and wireless networks.

Title: PhantomParasol: Parasol-type display for ambient and detailed information
Authors: Koji Tsukada, Toshiyuki Masui
Year: 2005
Abstract: This paper proposes a parasol-based display technique that integrates ambient and detailed information presentation. This paper demonstrates that a parasol-mounted LED matrix combined with device rotation and persistence-of-vision effects enables smooth control of information granularity to provide both distant ambient displays and near detailed displays for mobile users and nearby people.
Positioning Summary: This research addresses the importance of combining ambient and detailed information in mobile environments. This research positions itself as enabling smooth granularity control on a single handheld device to support mobile users by integrating ambient and detailed displays.
Purpose Summary: The objective of this work is to integrate ambient and detailed displays using a parasol-type display to bridge the gap in user display needs. The objective of this work targets mobile users and nearby people and aims to adjust information granularity according to reception load and usage context.
Method Summary: The system uses a parasol device equipped with multiple LED arrays, gyroscopic sensors, and an embedded microcontroller, and it presents detailed information by rotating the device to exploit persistence of vision. The system employs an LED matrix equivalent to 52×52, LED drivers, orientation/inclination sensors, and a microcontroller to convert BMP/JPG/PNG images into 52×52 displays, and it also considers integration with GPS and wireless networks.
